---
---

<section id="introduction" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">1. Introduction</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Your privacy is critically important to us. PennyWise is built with a
        private-first philosophy, ensuring that your financial data remains
        under your control. This Privacy Policy describes how PennyWise
        (&quot;we,&quot; &quot;us,&quot; or &quot;our&quot;) handles your
        information when you use our mobile application.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="collection" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <p>
          The following categories of information may be processed and stored 
          <strong class="text-foreground">only on your device</strong> to
          provide app features. PennyWise does not upload this information to
          our servers for storage.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-muted/30 border-border/50 rounded-xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-foreground mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-bold tracking-wider uppercase opacity-80">
            <span class="inline-flex text-primary size-5 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"/><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/></svg></span>
            2.1 User-Provided Information (Stored Locally)
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
              <span class="bg-primary mt-2 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
              <span>
                <strong class="text-foreground">
                  Profile Information:
                </strong> 
                Your name, preferred primary currency, and monthly budget
                settings.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
              <span class="bg-primary mt-2 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
              <span>
                <strong class="text-foreground">Financial Data:</strong> 
                Records of your income, expenses, categories, and payment card
                profiles (e.g., last four digits and card names).
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
              <span class="bg-primary mt-2 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
              <span>
                <strong class="text-foreground">
                  Notes and Attachments:
                </strong> 
                Optional notes or images (such as receipts) that you attach to
                your transactions.
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-muted/30 border-border/50 rounded-xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-foreground mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-bold tracking-wider uppercase opacity-80">
            <span class="inline-flex text-primary size-5 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="18" cy="5" r="3"/><circle cx="6" cy="12" r="3"/><circle cx="18" cy="19" r="3"/><line x1="8.59" x2="15.42" y1="13.51" y2="17.49"/><line x1="15.41" x2="8.59" y1="6.51" y2="10.49"/></svg></span>
            2.2 Device Permissions
          </h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed">
            To provide its core features, PennyWise may request access to:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
              <span class="bg-primary mt-2 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
              <span>
                <strong class="text-foreground">
                  Camera/Photo Library:
                </strong> 
                For capturing or selecting images of receipts to attach to
                transactions.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
              <span class="bg-primary mt-2 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
              <span>
                <strong class="text-foreground">
                  Biometrics (FaceID/Fingerprint):
                </strong> 
                To securely unlock the application.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
              <span class="bg-primary mt-2 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
              <span>
                <strong class="text-foreground">Notifications:</strong> To
                send budget alerts and reminders.
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="collection-use" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">3. Information Collection and Use</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p>
          PennyWise itself does not collect, store, or transmit any personal
          financial data to external servers or to the developer. Financial
          information you enter is stored only on your device.
        </p>
        <p>
          However, third-party services integrated into the app (such as Google
          AdMob) may collect certain information automatically for advertising
          purposes.
        </p>
        <p>
          PennyWise does not require user registration or account creation. We
          do not collect personally identifiable information such as email
          addresses or phone numbers.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="storage" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">4. Data Storage and Processing</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p>PennyWise is an offline-first application.</p>
        <p>
          PennyWise does not collect or store your financial data on external
          servers.
        </p>
        <p>
          However, the app may use third-party services (such as Google AdMob)
          which may collect limited device-level data.
        </p>
        <p>
          While PennyWise does not track your financial activity, advertising
          partners may collect limited technical data required to serve ads.
        </p>
        <div class="border-primary bg-primary/5 rounded-r-lg border-l-4 py-4 pl-6">
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground block">Local Storage:</strong>
              All your financial data, profile information, and attachments are
              stored locally on your device using encrypted and secure storage
              mechanisms (Hive and Flutter Secure Storage).
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground block">No Cloud Sync:</strong>
              By default, PennyWise does not transmit your personal or financial
              data to any external servers or cloud services operated by us. Your
              data remains on your device unless you choose to manually export
              or share it.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="advertising" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">5. Advertising</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="inline-flex text-primary mt-1 size-6 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m3 11 18-5v12L3 14v-3z"/><path d="M11.6 16.8a3 3 0 1 1-5.8-1.6"/></svg></span>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <p>
              This app uses Google AdMob, a mobile advertising service provided
              by Google.
            </p>
            <p>
              AdMob may collect certain information automatically, including:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>Device identifiers (such as advertising ID)</li>
              <li>IP address</li>
              <li>Device information</li>
              <li>Interaction data with ads</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              This information is used to provide and improve advertising
              services.
            </p>
            <p>
              You can learn more about how Google uses data here: 
              <a
                href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
                class="text-primary font-medium hover:underline"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                https://policies.google.com/privacy
              </a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="third-party" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">6. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p>
          The app may use third-party services that collect information used to
          identify you.
        </p>
        <p>These include:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>Google AdMob</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These services operate under their own privacy policies.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="consent" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">7. User Consent</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        By using the app, you agree to the use of third-party services as
        described in this policy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="use" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">8. Use of Information</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
          <span class="bg-primary mt-2 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>Provide financial tracking and visualization features.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
          <span class="bg-primary mt-2 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>
            Calculate and display budget progress and financial insights.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
          <span class="bg-primary mt-2 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>
            Secure your application access via PIN or biometric authentication.
          </span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="security" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">9. Security</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <span class="inline-flex text-primary mt-1 size-6 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="18" height="11" x="3" y="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg></span>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>
            We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your
            data locally:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground">On-Device Encryption:</strong> 
              Sensitive keys (like your PIN) are stored in the device&apos;s
              secure enclave/keystore.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground">
                Biometric Integration:
              </strong> 
              Biometric authentication is handled by your device&apos;s
              operating system. The app only receives a confirmation of
              successful authentication.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="rights" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">10. Your Data Rights</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p>
          Since your data is stored locally on your device, you have full
          control:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong class="text-foreground">Access & Modify:</strong> You
            can view and edit any entry directly within the app.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-foreground">Deletion:</strong> You can
            delete specific transactions, cards, or your entire data store from
            the settings menu within the app. All data can be permanently
            deleted by clearing app data or uninstalling the app.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="children" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">11. Children&apos;s Privacy</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        This app is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not
        knowingly collect personal information from children.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="changes" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you
        of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and
        updating the &quot;Last Updated&quot; date.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="contact" class="group scroll-mt-32">
  <div class="border-primary/20 relative border-l pl-6">
    <h2 class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary mb-6 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors">13. Contact Us</h2>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us
        at: 
        <a
          href="mailto:contact@adityatripathi.dev"
          class="text-primary font-medium hover:underline"
        >
          contact@adityatripathi.dev
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
